main event: The document discusses a proposed Congressional investigation into the U.S. Air Force's UFO program, known as Project Blue Book.
interesting points: The investigation was to be led by Congressman Joseph E. Karth of Minnesota and the House Science and Astronautics Committee.
The Air Force was preparing to provide witnesses, including Dr. J. Allen Hynek, the Air Force's UFO consultant, and Major Robert J. Friend, the chief of the Aerial Phenomena Branch.
Major Donald E. Keyhoe of the National Investigations Committee on Aerial Phenomena was suspected of being behind the push for the Congressional investigation.
Over 90% of UFO sightings were reportedly explainable according to the staff member who visited the Air Force's UFO program.
The Air Force briefed the Congressional staff member on their UFO investigation methods and data collection.
